description: From Latin nōnāgēnārius (“containing ninety”) + -an (“forming adjectives and representative nouns”), either directly or via French nonagénaire, from nonageni (“ninety each”) + -arius (“-ary”), from nonaginta (“nine tens, ninety”).

examples: Coordinate terms: vicenarian, tricenarian, quadragenarian, quinquagenarian, semicentenarian, hexagenerian, sexagenarian, septuagenarian, octogenarian, centenarian, semisupercentenarian, supercentenarian

entries.meaning: Synonym of ninetysomething: a person between 90 and 99 years old.
